<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,150,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,223,249]" pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Notes.</emphasis>
Individuals of this species are attracted to light. An example of the habitat of this species can be seen in 
<figureCitation box="[151,232,259,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1957,1981]" captionTargetBox="[212,1375,1051,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-251@6.[212,1375,1051,1933]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Example of habitats for Oedemeridae in Oman. 4a: Wahiba sandy dunes (Alloxantha talhouki); 4b: Al Rajmi (Nacerdochroa carinatopyga, Alloxantha flava); 4c: Shinas (Probosca (Proboxantha) fuscipennis); 4d: Wadi Damm (N. carinatopyga, A. flava)." pageId="6" pageNumber="427">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
